quran[25]{c,v,t}:
  55,1,The Beneficent Allah
  55,2,Taught (Has made known) the Quran
  55,3,He created man
  55,4,"Taught him speech (language, modes of expression and communication)"
  55,5,The sun and the moon follow courses (exactly) reckoned (in space and time)
  55,6,And the stars (or herds of animals) and the trees do adore (Him)
  55,7,"And the heaven, He raised it high, and He made the Balance (or set the measure)"
  55,8,That you may not exceed the measure (or transgress beyond limits)
  55,9,But keep the measure strictly (with justice or equity) nor fall short of it (or be deficient in measuring)
  55,10,"And the earth, has He set out for (His) creatures"
  55,11,Therein is fruit and palms having sheathed clusters
  55,12,And the grain with its husk and fragrant herbs
  55,13,"Which then of the bounties (favours, gifts)) of your Lord will you deny"
  55,14,He created man from dry clay like earthen vessels (as containers)
  55,15,And He created the jinn of a flame of (or of smokeless) fire
  55,16,Which then of the bounties of your Lord will you deny
  55,17,He is the Lord of the two Easts and Lord of the two Wests
  55,18,Which then of the bounties of your Lord will you deny
  55,19,"He has made the two seas (streams or bodies of water, salt and sweet) to flow freely so that they meet together"
  55,20,Between them is a barrier which they do not transgress
  55,21,Which then of the bounties of your Lord will you deny
  55,22,There come forth from them pearls and coral
  55,23,Which then of the bounties of your Lord will you deny
  55,24,And His are the ships reared aloft in the sea like mountains
  55,25,Which then of the bounties of your Lord will you deny